In the PID controller (likely pid.cpp or equivalent):
1. Add integral clamping:
   integral += error * dt;
   integral = std::clamp(integral, -INTEGRAL_MAX, INTEGRAL_MAX);
2. Add conditional integration (stop accumulating when output is saturated):
   if (output < OUTPUT_MAX && output > OUTPUT_MIN) {
     integral += error * dt;
   }
3. Optionally implement back-calculation anti-windup:
   integral += (Ki * error + Kb * (saturated_output - raw_output)) * dt;
   where Kb is the back-calculation gain (typically 1/Ti).
4. Review and potentially reduce Ki to prevent rapid windup on step changes in reference.
